  "prompt": "How do you drop off a U-Haul at a different location?",
  "response": "Dropping off a U-Haul at a different location than where you picked it up is known as a \"one-way\" rental. Here\u2019s how to do it:\n\n### 1. **Reserve a One-Way Rental**\n   - When booking your U-Haul, specify that you need a one-way rental. This ensures the truck is available at your starting location and authorized for drop-off at the destination.\n   - Check availability for one-way rentals, as not all locations or times may allow it.\n\n### 2. **Confirm Drop-Off Location**\n   - During booking, select the drop-off location. U-Haul will confirm whether the location can accept your vehicle.\n   - Ensure the drop-off location is open and operational during your planned return time.\n\n### 3. **Understand the Fees**\n   - One-way rentals typically incur additional fees based on the distance between pick-up and drop-off locations. These fees will be outlined during your reservation.\n\n### 4. **Return the U-Haul**\n   - Arrive at the drop-off location during its business hours.\n   - Park the vehicle in the designated return area.\n   - Clean out the truck and remove all personal belongings.\n   - Take photos of the truck\u2019s condition for your records.\n\n### 5. **Complete the Return Process**\n   - Go inside the drop-off location or use the U-Haul app to complete the return process.\n   - Provide the necessary mileage, fuel level, and any other details requested.\n   - Get a receipt or confirmation of the return.\n\n### 6. **Keep Documentation**\n   - Retain the return receipt and any other paperwork until you confirm your rental account is closed and all charges are accurate.\n\nIf you have any questions or specific concerns, contact U-Haul customer service or the location directly before your drop-off.",
